00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:38,051
where they were actually killed.

98
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:39,885
It sure sounds
like aragami to me.

99
00:06:40,774 --> 00:06:42,094
Yeah, that's about
what I figured.

100
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:43,696
Aragami.

101
00:06:43,777 --> 00:06:45,340
As soon as I heard
about these incidents,

102
00:06:45,364 --> 00:06:47,724
I just knew they would fall
under your area of jurisdiction.

103
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:50,494
And that's why you ran all
the way over here, huh,

104
00:06:51,328 --> 00:06:52,328
not to see Takeuchi, eh?

105
00:06:53,289 --> 00:06:54,289
(laughing nervously)

106
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:57,958
Nitwit.

107
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:00,793
Huh?

108
00:07:00,794 --> 00:07:01,995
By the way, where's your boss?

109
00:07:02,213 --> 00:07:03,494
We're really not allowed to say.

110
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,605
Mr. Kunikida has
something important to do.

111
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:10,220
